00:43:28,500 --> 00:43:30,500
"and no one could enter the temple

759
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:34,100
until the seven plagues
of the seven angels were completed."

760
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:36,500
Well, what are you saying?

761
00:43:36,600 --> 00:43:37,900
What are you proposing?

762
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:39,600
That we all prepare...

763
00:43:41,100 --> 00:43:42,500
to meet our Maker.

764
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:44,700
JIM: Oh, prepare to meet shit!

765
00:43:45,700 --> 00:43:48,300
Lady, your tongue
must be hung in the middle

766
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:50,200
so that it can waggle at both ends.

767
00:43:50,300 --> 00:43:52,100
MRS. CARMODY:
The end time has come,

768
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:53,900
not in flames, but in mist.

769
00:43:53,900 --> 00:43:55,000
JIM: Come here!

770
00:43:55,100 --> 00:43:56,200
MYRON: Easy! Back off!

771
00:43:56,300 --> 00:43:59,700
How about if your ass prepares
to meet my size-10 work boot.

772
00:43:59,700 --> 00:44:02,200
- How about that?
- Hey, there's no call for that.

773
00:44:02,300 --> 00:44:04,500
Myron, please,
calm your friend down.

774
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:07,400
MRS. CARMODY: I'm trying
to save your soul, you stupid man.

775
00:44:07,500 --> 00:44:09,700
- Doubters will doubt till the end.
- It's okay.

776
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:10,800
No, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

777
00:44:10,900 --> 00:44:13,500
A monstrosity <i>did</i> pull
that poor boy away.

778
00:44:14,100 --> 00:44:17,400
Things in the mist--
do you doubt?

779
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:18,600
Do you?

780
00:44:20,100 --> 00:44:22,000
Then go out.

781
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:24,400
Go out and say,
"How do you do."

782
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:25,600
Shut up, lady.

783
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:28,400
For God's sakes.

784
00:44:28,500 --> 00:44:30,700
Look, you'll have to stop now.
You're scaring the children.

785
00:44:30,700 --> 00:44:32,200
They should be scared.

786
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:34,900
Oh, yes, they should.

787
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:38,400
Their beautiful, pure little minds

788
00:44:38,500 --> 00:44:40,900
have been corrupted with lies.

789
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:42,000
Lies.

790
00:44:42,100 --> 00:44:44,200
All this talk of a modern God,

791
00:44:44,300 --> 00:44:47,000
or no God.

792
00:44:47,100 --> 00:44:48,800
There is one God.

793
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:50,500
The God of the Israelites.

794
00:44:50,500 --> 00:44:53,400
And He is a stern and vengeful God,

795
00:44:53,500 --> 00:44:56,000
and we have been mocking Him
far too long,

796
00:44:56,100 --> 00:44:59,700
and now He demands
retribution in blood.

797
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:02,500
It is time to declare yourselves.

798
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:04,200
Take sides--

799
00:45:04,300 --> 00:45:06,100
the saved and the damned.

800
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:09,700
Read the Good Book.
It calls for expiation.

801
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:11,600
- Blood!
- What?

802
00:45:11,700 --> 00:45:12,800
Blood.

803
00:45:13,900 --> 00:45:15,500
Little Normie was first,

804
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:18,700
and now God calls the rest of us.

805
00:45:18,700 --> 00:45:20,200
The bill is due.

806
00:45:20,300 --> 00:45:21,800
It must be paid.

807
00:45:21,900 --> 00:45:24,900
As Abraham prepared
to sacrifice his only son

808
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:26,800
to prove his love for God, so--

809
00:45:26,900 --> 00:45:28,300
- Enough.
- ( onlookers gasp )

810
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:36,400
- Ohh.
- Another down payment.

811
00:45:36,500 --> 00:45:38,400
A few more pennies in the jar.

812
00:45:38,500 --> 00:45:41,000
Now, that's nice, see.
I can't smack her, but it's okay for you.

813
00:45:41,100 --> 00:45:42,300
I-I'm sorry everybody,

814
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:45,400
but this lady's perspective is
a little too Old Testament for my taste.

815
00:45:45,500 --> 00:45:47,000
MRS. CARMODY:
They'll come for you.

816
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:50,500
Maybe tonight,
when darkness comes.

817
00:45:52,100 --> 00:45:54,900
They'll come tonight,
and they'll take someone else.

818
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:57,000
See if they don't.

819
00:45:57,100 --> 00:45:58,900
And when they do,

820
00:45:58,900 --> 00:46:01,500
you will cry to God,

821
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:05,300
and you will beg Mother Carmody
to show you the way.

822
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:06,700
OLLIE: That's fine.

823
00:46:07,700 --> 00:46:10,000
But until then,
if you don't shut up,

824
00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:12,100
I'll wrap this tape around your mouth.

825
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:14,500
You just try it, Ollie Weeks.

826
00:46:14,500 --> 00:46:16,000
And you, bitch...

827
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:19,100
you hit me again...

828
00:46:20,100 --> 00:46:22,100
if you dare.

829
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:24,900
You'll be on your knees to me
before this is through.

830
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:36,300
Those of you who aren't local should know
that Mrs. Carmody is known in town for being...

831
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:38,600
unstable.

832
00:46:38,700 --> 00:46:41,900
No shit.
What was your first clue?

833
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:46,400
SOLDIER: Shh.

834
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:50,400
- Hi.
- What's up, little dude?

835
00:46:50,500 --> 00:46:52,300
How come your friends
don't come get us?

836
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,000
They got tanks and stuff, right?

837
00:46:55,400 --> 00:46:56,800
Why can't you just call 'em?

838
00:46:56,900 --> 00:46:58,000
Phones don't work.

839
00:46:58,100 --> 00:46:59,900
But don't you got, like, a radio?

840
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,400
Hey, champ, what's going on?

841
00:47:01,500 --> 00:47:03,700
I want their friends
to come rescue us.

842
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:05,900
They would if they could, pal.
They're stuck here just like us.

843
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:06,800
- But--
- Shh.

844
00:47:06,900 --> 00:47:08,600
Now, guys, we could use
a hand over there.

845
00:47:08,700 --> 00:47:09,800
SOLDIER: Yeah, sure thing.

846
00:47:09,900 --> 00:47:11,600
SOLDIER #2:
Troop, off your asses.

847
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:14,400
- DAVID: You all right?
- I don't like that scary lady.

848
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:16,800
Oh, man, I don't either.

849
00:47:16,900 --> 00:47:18,400
But you know what?

850
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:21,200
Maybe she's scared too.

851
00:47:22,200 --> 00:47:23,200
You think?

852
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,700
You think Mommy's okay?

853
00:47:26,700 --> 00:47:29,000
( sighs ) Billy...

854
00:47:32,000 --> 00:47:34,000
I'm sorry about the times
I was bad to her.

855
00:47:34,100 --> 00:47:35,200
Aw, hey.

856
00:47:36,200 --> 00:47:39,300
Mommy loves you very much.

857
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:40,900
And I'll bet she's fine.

858
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:44,700
And I promise you,

859
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:48,000
I'm gonna do everything I can
to get us back to her.

860
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:51,000
- Okay?
- 'Kay.

861
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:53,400
- Yeah?
- 'Kay.

862
00:47:54,500 --> 00:47:58,500
So, we can use the charcoal fluid
and the mops to make torches.

863
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:00,600
And we've got knives and stuff, God knows.

864
00:48:00,700 --> 00:48:05,900
This may be a silly question, Bud,
but... do you happen to have a <i>gun</i> in the store?

865
00:48:06,900 --> 00:48:08,700
Here? No. Please.

866
00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:10,600
This-- this isn't Los Angeles.

867
00:48:10,700 --> 00:48:12,300
I've got a shotgun in my truck.

868
00:48:13,700 --> 00:48:15,100
I could try for it if you want.

869
00:48:15,200 --> 00:48:17,500
Oh, God, I don't think that'd be
a good idea, Mr. Cornell.

870
00:48:17,500 --> 00:48:18,600
Hold on.

871
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:22,500
This gun, um...

872
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:24,400
my husband's idea.

873
00:48:24,500 --> 00:48:26,500
He's away on business a lot.

874
00:48:26,600 --> 00:48:27,800
It's not even loaded.

875
00:48:27,800 --> 00:48:29,500
Ain't much use unloaded, ma'am.

876
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:30,600
AMANDA: Um...

877
00:48:34,200 --> 00:48:35,700
DAVID:
You know how to use that?

878
00:48:35,800 --> 00:48:39,600
Well, I shot it once on a pistol range.
Hit the target a few times.

879
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:42,400
So, we got a gun.

880
00:48:42,500 --> 00:48:44,400
Anybody know how to shoot it?

881
00:48:44,500 --> 00:48:45,900
<i>Well,</i> I mean?

882
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,000
I do.

883
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:50,800
You?

884
00:48:50,900 --> 00:48:53,700
( scoffs )
Ollie. Please.

885
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:00,900
Some target shooting.

886
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:03,200
State champion in '94.

887
00:49:03,300 --> 00:49:06,900
- MAN: You're crazy if you go out there!
- NORTON: Let us pass! Let us pass, please!

888
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:08,200
Let's just talk this thing through.

889
00:49:08,300 --> 00:49:10,500
NORTON: We have, and we've
made our decision. We're leaving.

890
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:13,500
Hey, Mr. Mackey's gonna barbecue
some chicken on the gas grill.

891
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:15,900
- Why don't we just sit down and just--
- What, and let you keep on talking?

892
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,100
No, I've been in far too many
courtrooms to fall for that.

893
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:20,200
You've already psyched out
half a dozen of my people already.

894
00:49:20,300 --> 00:49:21,400
AMANDA: <i>Your</i> people?

895
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:23,200
What kind of talk is that?
They're people, that's all.

896
00:49:23,300 --> 00:49:24,800
Now-- now listen, everyone.

897
00:49:24,900 --> 00:49:27,800
We are experiencing
some kind of disaster.

898
00:49:27,900 --> 00:49:29,900
I don't know whether
it's manmade or natural,

899
00:49:29,900 --> 00:49:33,800
but I do know that
it's definitely not supernatural

900
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:36,200
or biblical,
and, no offense, Mrs. Carmody,

901
00:49:36,300 --> 00:49:38,000
but the only way
we're gonna help ourselves

902
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,700
is to seek rescue.

903
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:42,500
We're going out.

904
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:47,300
- Brent, look.
- I'm not discussing this any further.

905
00:49:47,300 --> 00:49:49,500
I know. I just want to ask a favor.

906
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:52,800
Tie this around your waist.

907
00:49:52,800 --> 00:49:53,900
What for?

908
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:56,100
It'll let us know you got
at least 300 feet.

909
00:49:58,400 --> 00:49:59,400
I'll do it.

910
00:50:00,900 --> 00:50:04,500
- Are you throwing in with them?
- Me? No thanks.

911
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:07,200
I think your man there
is a little too tightly wound.

912
00:50:07,300 --> 00:50:09,400
Gonna get somebody killed.

913
00:50:09,500 --> 00:50:12,300
But I'm thinkin' we could use
that shotgun of yours.

914
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:15,000
I saw where you parked
when I pulled in.

915
00:50:15,100 --> 00:50:17,200
Red pickup, right?
Far entrance?

916
00:50:17,300 --> 00:50:20,100
Son, you got brass balls.

917
00:50:20,200 --> 00:50:22,100
The shells are
in the glove compartment.

918
00:50:22,200 --> 00:50:23,400
Drive it back.

919
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:26,800
All right.

920
00:50:26,900 --> 00:50:28,600
Just see they're paying out this line.

921
00:50:28,700 --> 00:50:30,900
Line's up, I'll cut her loose,

922
00:50:31,000 --> 00:50:32,300
just so you understand.

923
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:33,500
DAVID: Yeah.

924
00:50:41,100 --> 00:50:43,400
You sure there's no way
I can talk you out of this?

925
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:48,800
David... there's nothing out there.
Nothing in the mist.

926
00:50:48,900 --> 00:50:50,800
What if you're wrong?

927
00:50:51,900 --> 00:50:53,400
Then, I guess...

928
00:50:55,500 --> 00:50:58,500
the joke would be on me after all.

929
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:05,000
We're gonna send back help.

930
00:51:06,100 --> 00:51:08,500
You'll die out there.
All of you.

931
00:51:21,200 --> 00:51:24,400
Hey, crazy lady,
I believe in God too.

932
00:51:24,500 --> 00:51:28,500
I just don't think He's the bloodthirsty asshole
you make Him out to be.

933
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:31,200
Well, you take that up with the devil
when you run into him.

934
00:51:31,300 --> 00:51:32,900
You just chat it over at your leisure.

935
00:51:41,600 --> 00:51:43,500
Well, let's strike out
toward the center of town.

936
00:52:02,700 --> 00:52:04,000
Keep it loose.

937
00:52:19,800 --> 00:52:21,300
DAVID: Nice and easy.

938
00:52:21,400 --> 00:52:22,600
OLLIE: ( low ) Keep going.

939
00:52:25,200 --> 00:52:26,600
( onlookers murmur )

940
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:41,300
JIM: Look.

941
00:52:44,400 --> 00:52:45,700
It's going.

942
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:48,900
They're doing good.

943
00:52:50,900 --> 00:52:52,600
Aah! Aaahhhh!

944
00:52:52,700 --> 00:52:54,800
( onlookers screaming )

945
00:53:00,700 --> 00:53:02,200
( cord whistles sharply )

946
00:53:07,000 --> 00:53:08,300
MAN: Put it down!

947
00:53:09,300 --> 00:53:11,600
Ohh! Pull!

948
00:53:13,500 --> 00:53:15,900
MAN: Oh, my God!
I'm slippin'!

949
00:53:17,400 --> 00:53:19,700
Pull! Back up! Back up!
Back up!

950
00:53:30,600 --> 00:53:33,000
( onlookers scream and shout )

951
00:53:33,100 --> 00:53:34,200
Get it off!

952
00:53:43,500 --> 00:53:44,600
Oh, my God.

953
00:53:49,500 --> 00:53:51,200
( woman sobbing )

954
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:52,700
- JIM: Aw, sh--
- MRS. CARMODY: Blood!

955
00:53:52,800 --> 00:53:54,500
Awww, sh--!

956
00:53:54,600 --> 00:53:56,300
MRS. CARMODY:
Oh, my God!

957
00:53:57,500 --> 00:53:59,800
- ( onlookers shouting )
- Oh, my God!

958
00:54:07,100 --> 00:54:09,000
( onlookers screaming )

959
00:54:14,300 --> 00:54:15,600
Cut the rope!

960
00:54:18,400 --> 00:54:19,300
Shut the door!

961
00:54:25,000 --> 00:54:27,000
Now do you see?

962
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:30,500
Now do you believe?

963
00:54:40,100 --> 00:54:41,900
OLLIE:
About a half-hour of daylight left.

964
00:54:43,200 --> 00:54:45,100
Guys, how's it going
with these work lights?

965
00:54:45,100 --> 00:54:48,700
- We're gettin' 'em rigged up all right.
- Yeah, check it out.

966
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:50,700
All right, all right.
Save it, save it.

967
00:54:51,700 --> 00:54:53,200
These batteries ain't topped up.

968
00:54:53,300 --> 00:54:55,400
You turn the lights on,
it's gonna drain 'em quick.

969
00:54:55,500 --> 00:54:56,600
How quick?

970
00:54:56,700 --> 00:54:58,700
- Five minutes, maybe ten.
- Yeah, if that.

971
00:54:58,700 --> 00:55:00,700
Okay, emergencies only.

972
00:55:01,700 --> 00:55:03,200
If something gets in the store.

973
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:13,500
( sighs ) Holy Jesus,
you scared the shit outta me.

974
00:55:13,600 --> 00:55:15,200
Oh, Sally, I'm sorry, really.

975
00:55:16,700 --> 00:55:19,500
I thought I'd come in and say hi
and see how you were holding up.

976
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:21,100
- Hi.
- Hi.

977
00:55:22,200 --> 00:55:23,500
Barely. How about you?

978
00:55:23,600 --> 00:55:25,200
I'm worried about my folks, I guess.

979
00:55:25,300 --> 00:55:27,900
You know, they live
up on Shorm Road.

980
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:30,100
That's less than
five miles from here.

981
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:31,700
How 'bout yours?

982
00:55:31,800 --> 00:55:33,400
Well, they're out of town right now.

983
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:37,000
They're at my aunt's in Boston, so...

984
00:55:37,100 --> 00:55:39,800
That's lucky.
That means they're okay.

985
00:55:39,900 --> 00:55:41,200
I hope so.

986
00:55:43,400 --> 00:55:47,000
So... how soon you shipping out?

987
00:55:47,100 --> 00:55:48,700
Uh, couple weeks.

988
00:55:50,400 --> 00:55:51,900
Scared about going over there?

989
00:55:53,300 --> 00:55:54,300
( softly ) Yeah.

990
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:01,100
- Hey, Wayne?
- Hmm?

991
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:04,300
How come you never asked me out?

992
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:07,300
We flirted all through high school.
I know you like me.

993
00:56:07,300 --> 00:56:08,500
( chuckles )

994
00:56:11,600 --> 00:56:13,100
So how come?

995
00:56:15,500 --> 00:56:17,400
I'm stupid, I guess.

996
00:56:33,900 --> 00:56:36,100
Oh, shit! I'm sorry.

997
00:56:36,200 --> 00:56:40,500
Don't be. I just-- I just didn't really want it
to happen like this, you know?

998
00:56:40,500 --> 00:56:43,200
Some shitty locker room at work.

999
00:56:43,300 --> 00:56:45,500
Can we just stay in here a while, then?

1000
00:56:46,900 --> 00:56:49,300
I mean, just-- just you and me.

1001
00:57:00,600 --> 00:57:04,200
- DAN: The parking lot lamps turned on.
- OLLIE: They're on a timer.

1002
00:57:04,300 --> 00:57:06,300
Must be a different municipal line.

1003
00:57:06,400 --> 00:57:09,100
DAN: Maybe we could
tie into them somehow,

1004
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:11,000
get some electricity in here.

1005
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:13,700
That'd mean walking out the door.

1006
00:57:24,700 --> 00:57:26,500
- Gaaaahhhh! God!
- ( woman screams )

1007
00:57:27,300 --> 00:57:28,800
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

1008
00:57:28,800 --> 00:57:30,800
- OLLIE: David! David!
- ( indistinct )

1009
00:57:33,100 --> 00:57:34,200
WOMAN:...you sure?

1010
