1506
01:26:29,100 --> 01:26:34,300
That poor girl is dead,
and that boy is burnt in the back room!

1507
01:26:34,400 --> 01:26:38,300
She's got 'em believing she's a psychic;
she has a direct line with God.

1508
01:26:38,300 --> 01:26:40,800
Why wouldn't they?
Woman never shuts up.

1509
01:26:40,900 --> 01:26:43,200
Like those speeches
Castro used to make.

1510
01:26:43,300 --> 01:26:45,900
( Carmody's followers applauds )

1511
01:26:46,000 --> 01:26:49,300
Ollie says you're thinking of leaving.

1512
01:26:49,400 --> 01:26:50,700
I'm in.

1513
01:26:50,800 --> 01:26:52,700
DAVID: No. Sorry.

1514
01:26:52,800 --> 01:26:56,600
I mean, come on, you saw what
happened to Bobby... Mike...

1515
01:26:56,700 --> 01:27:00,400
I won't... do that again.
I won't be responsible.

1516
01:27:00,500 --> 01:27:02,000
You might want to reconsider that.

1517
01:27:02,100 --> 01:27:05,400
MRS. CARMODY: What will-- what will keep
these evil, these abominations at bay?

1518
01:27:05,500 --> 01:27:07,000
What will keep them away?

1519
01:27:07,100 --> 01:27:10,000
"The rock will not hide them.
The dead tree gives no shelter."

1520
01:27:10,000 --> 01:27:11,500
What will end it?
Let me hear it.

1521
01:27:11,600 --> 01:27:13,600
- Expiation!
- So what are we talking about?

1522
01:27:13,700 --> 01:27:16,200
- Expiation!
- Yeah, say it again like you mean it!

1523
01:27:16,300 --> 01:27:17,500
Expiation!

1524
01:27:17,600 --> 01:27:22,600
Welcome to <i>Sesame Street.</i>
Today's word is "expiation."

1525
01:27:22,700 --> 01:27:24,800
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

1526
01:27:24,800 --> 01:27:27,400
That boy hasn't been right
since the pharmacy.

1527
01:27:27,500 --> 01:27:30,500
His mind's just snapped. Gone.

1528
01:27:30,600 --> 01:27:32,200
Hasn't even been two days.

1529
01:27:33,200 --> 01:27:34,700
Not even two days.

1530
01:27:34,800 --> 01:27:37,400
CORNELL: I'm not spendin' the rest
of my life here, I'll tell you what.

1531
01:27:37,400 --> 01:27:40,100
OLLIE: I can quietly gather up
some bags of groceries

1532
01:27:40,200 --> 01:27:43,500
and hide them up at one of
the check stands by the door.

1533
01:27:43,600 --> 01:27:45,900
DAN: It was your idea.
It's your vehicle.

1534
01:27:46,000 --> 01:27:47,500
It'll be your call.

1535
01:27:49,400 --> 01:27:51,900
I'd rather die out there trying
than in here waiting.

1536
01:27:52,000 --> 01:27:54,000
( followers applaud )

1537
01:27:54,000 --> 01:27:56,300
MRS. CARMODY:
Who will save them? No one.

1538
01:27:56,400 --> 01:27:59,500
These rocks <i>will</i> not hide them.

1539
01:27:59,500 --> 01:28:04,300
I want some idea of what we're up against.
I want to know what this mist is.

1540
01:28:05,300 --> 01:28:08,200
- I want to talk to the soldiers.
- Soldiers? What's that gonna do?

1541
01:28:08,300 --> 01:28:10,400
You heard what that M.P. said
at the pharmacy.

1542
01:28:10,500 --> 01:28:12,800
David, I'm not even sure
I knew he was talking.

1543
01:28:12,900 --> 01:28:14,600
The situation was insane.

1544
01:28:14,600 --> 01:28:16,400
He said he was sorry.

1545
01:28:16,500 --> 01:28:18,500
Wasn't that the word
he used-- "sorry"?

1546
01:28:18,600 --> 01:28:20,900
That's right.
He said it was their fault, right?

1547
01:28:20,900 --> 01:28:24,800
- AMANDA: What did he mean by that?
- That's what we're gonna find out.

1548
01:28:24,900 --> 01:28:26,500
Irene, stay with Billy, please.

1549
01:28:26,600 --> 01:28:27,900
MRS. CARMODY:
Verse 17!

1550
01:28:28,000 --> 01:28:30,500
"...poured out his vial into the air,

1551
01:28:30,500 --> 01:28:32,400
"and there came a great voice

1552
01:28:32,500 --> 01:28:35,200
"out of the temple of heaven
from the throne, saying,

1553
01:28:35,300 --> 01:28:37,800
" 'It is done! It is done!'

1554
01:28:37,900 --> 01:28:41,100
"And there were voices
and lightning,

1555
01:28:41,200 --> 01:28:44,200
and thunders,
and a great earthquake."

1556
01:28:44,300 --> 01:28:47,000
Yes! Come to me!

1557
01:28:47,100 --> 01:28:48,200
WAYNE: What?

1558
01:28:48,300 --> 01:28:50,500
- Where's your friends?
- I ain't seen 'em.

1559
01:28:50,600 --> 01:28:52,900
Not that big a store.
It's kinda hard to lose.

1560
01:28:52,900 --> 01:28:55,900
I ain't seen 'em, I said.
I look like their keeper?

1561
01:28:59,100 --> 01:29:02,000
- What do you want from me?
- What do you know about this mist?

1562
01:29:02,100 --> 01:29:04,500
I don't know nothin'.
I got nothin' to do with it.

1563
01:29:04,600 --> 01:29:08,400
That's not what the M.P. said in the pharmacy
before the spiders came out of his skin.

1564
01:29:09,800 --> 01:29:11,600
They're not in the store.

1565
01:29:11,700 --> 01:29:14,800
The only place we haven't looked
is the loading dock.

1566
01:29:14,900 --> 01:29:16,000
...because you know.

1567
01:29:16,000 --> 01:29:18,100
You saw the good face
of God tonight.

1568
01:29:18,200 --> 01:29:19,500
Yes? Tell us.

1569
01:29:19,500 --> 01:29:21,800
Here is an old man who has seen!

1570
01:29:21,800 --> 01:29:24,000
- Yes, he has <i>seen!</i>
- ( applauding )

1571
01:29:24,000 --> 01:29:25,100
MAN: Amen.

1572
01:29:25,200 --> 01:29:28,800
MRS. CARMODY: And I <i>want</i> to say,
do I want to walk with you

1573
01:29:28,900 --> 01:29:31,600
into my Father's hands?

1574
01:29:32,100 --> 01:29:33,100
Morales.

1575
01:29:34,100 --> 01:29:35,200
Donaldson.

1576
01:29:37,800 --> 01:29:39,000
Guys...

1577
01:29:41,200 --> 01:29:44,700
- It's the only place they can be.
- WAYNE: What?

1578
01:29:44,800 --> 01:29:46,200
OLLIE: Couldn't just disappear.

1579
01:29:46,300 --> 01:29:49,300
WAYNE: Look, I told you,
okay, I don't know where they are--

1580
01:29:49,400 --> 01:29:51,500
( sharp gasp )

1581
01:29:56,400 --> 01:29:58,100
I didn't think they'd do it.

1582
01:29:58,200 --> 01:30:00,500
They said they would do it, and I just--

1583
01:30:00,600 --> 01:30:04,000
I told them what the M.P. said at the pharmacy,
and they swore they'd do it.

1584
01:30:04,000 --> 01:30:06,800
I just-- I didn't think they would. Oh, Jesus!

1585
01:30:06,900 --> 01:30:10,100
It's the Arrowhead Project, isn't it?

1586
01:30:10,100 --> 01:30:13,600
This mist, it's some kind of,
what, military fuckup?

1587
01:30:13,700 --> 01:30:15,400
What were you guys
messin' with up there, huh?

1588
01:30:15,500 --> 01:30:18,300
We got you now,
you sorry son of a bitch!

1589
01:30:18,400 --> 01:30:19,400
Get in there!

1590
01:30:19,500 --> 01:30:22,400
It was them!
It was them what done it to us!

1591
01:30:22,500 --> 01:30:26,000
It was them what brung down
the final wrath upon us!

1592
01:30:26,100 --> 01:30:28,500
Those two peckerwoods
that he's been with this whole time,

1593
01:30:28,600 --> 01:30:30,900
they hung themselves in the back
because they knew!

1594
01:30:31,000 --> 01:30:32,500
They knew it all along!

1595
01:30:32,600 --> 01:30:34,500
- He's crazy. He doesn't know--
- Get on your knees!

1596
01:30:34,500 --> 01:30:35,800
- ( shouting )
- MAN: Stay out of it, Drayton!

1597
01:30:35,900 --> 01:30:38,000
They heard it too, didn't you?
All of ya!

1598
01:30:38,000 --> 01:30:41,500
All about the Arrowhead Project
and all that secret shit up on the mountain.

1599
01:30:41,500 --> 01:30:43,000
That's what brung it down on us.

1600
01:30:43,100 --> 01:30:45,200
That's what brung down the wrath of God!

1601
01:30:45,300 --> 01:30:46,300
MRS. CARMODY: Oh!

1602
01:30:48,100 --> 01:30:50,100
Private Jessup.

1603
01:30:51,900 --> 01:30:53,100
It wasn't <i>me.</i>

1604
01:30:53,200 --> 01:30:55,500
I'm just--
I'm <i>stationed</i> up there.

1605
01:30:55,600 --> 01:30:57,000
I'm not responsible--

1606
01:30:57,100 --> 01:30:58,700
- Bullshit!
- Hell, I'm a local!

1607
01:30:58,800 --> 01:31:00,800
Most of you people know me.

1608
01:31:00,900 --> 01:31:06,000
You stop your chicken shit whining
or I will cut your puling tongue out.

1609
01:31:06,100 --> 01:31:07,700
Now you tell us!

1610
01:31:07,800 --> 01:31:09,100
( coughs )

1611
01:31:09,200 --> 01:31:10,900
MRS. CARMODY: Tell us.

1612
01:31:10,900 --> 01:31:13,600
Look, look. Okay, okay.

1613
01:31:13,700 --> 01:31:15,100
I heard stuff.

1614
01:31:15,200 --> 01:31:16,500
Stuff?

1615
01:31:16,600 --> 01:31:18,600
Yes, we all heard stuff.

1616
01:31:19,900 --> 01:31:23,700
Like how they, um...

1617
01:31:23,800 --> 01:31:25,800
how they thought
that there were other dimensions,

1618
01:31:25,900 --> 01:31:28,700
you know, other--
other worlds all around us,

1619
01:31:28,800 --> 01:31:31,300
and how they wanted
to try and make, um,

1620
01:31:31,400 --> 01:31:32,800
a window--

1621
01:31:32,900 --> 01:31:35,600
you know, so they could look through
and see what's on the other side.

1622
01:31:37,800 --> 01:31:40,500
Well, maybe your window
turned out to be a door. Didn't it?

1623
01:31:40,600 --> 01:31:42,400
Not mine! Those scientists'!

1624
01:31:42,500 --> 01:31:45,100
- Oh, the scientists!
- Yes, the scientists!

1625
01:31:45,100 --> 01:31:47,200
They must have ripped
a hole open by accident.

1626
01:31:47,300 --> 01:31:49,100
This other world
came spilling through to ours.

1627
01:31:49,200 --> 01:31:52,500
That's what Donaldson was saying
to me right before he killed himself.

1628
01:31:52,600 --> 01:31:54,600
I didn't understand the half of it.

1629
01:31:56,500 --> 01:31:58,100
It ain't my fault!

1630
01:31:58,200 --> 01:31:59,200
Oh.

1631
01:32:00,300 --> 01:32:03,600
Ain't. His. Fault.

1632
01:32:03,700 --> 01:32:06,200
- ( angry murmuring )
- No, no, no.

1633
01:32:06,300 --> 01:32:10,300
Ain't nothin' ever anybody's fault.

1634
01:32:10,400 --> 01:32:12,700
But he denies it.

1635
01:32:12,800 --> 01:32:15,300
He points the finger,

1636
01:32:15,300 --> 01:32:18,500
this Judas in our midst.

1637
01:32:18,600 --> 01:32:19,600
CROWD: Judas!

1638
01:32:19,700 --> 01:32:21,400
David!

1639
01:32:21,500 --> 01:32:23,800
You! You!

1640
01:32:23,900 --> 01:32:25,800
Don't you know by now?

1641
01:32:25,900 --> 01:32:27,900
Don't you know the truth?

1642
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:30,600
We are being punished.

1643
01:32:30,700 --> 01:32:34,200
For what? For going
against the will of God!

1644
01:32:34,300 --> 01:32:38,600
For going against
His forbidden rules of old!

1645
01:32:38,700 --> 01:32:40,100
Walking on the moon!

1646
01:32:40,200 --> 01:32:41,700
Yes! Yes!

1647
01:32:41,800 --> 01:32:44,700
- Or-- or splitting His atoms!
- MAN: Amen!

1648
01:32:44,700 --> 01:32:49,500
Or-- or-- or stem cells and abortions!

1649
01:32:49,500 --> 01:32:52,500
And destroying the secrets of life

1650
01:32:52,600 --> 01:32:55,800
that only God above has any right to!

1651
01:32:55,900 --> 01:32:57,400
Amen! Amen!

1652
01:32:57,500 --> 01:33:00,100
MRS. CARMODY:
Yes, I know! It is true!

1653
01:33:00,100 --> 01:33:02,700
And now we are being punished.

1654
01:33:02,800 --> 01:33:05,700
The judgment is being
brought down upon us.

1655
01:33:05,800 --> 01:33:08,400
The fiends of hell,
you see they are let loose,

1656
01:33:08,500 --> 01:33:12,200
and star Wormwood blazes!

1657
01:33:12,200 --> 01:33:13,500
And it is his fault!

1658
01:33:13,600 --> 01:33:16,900
No! No! It is not my fault! No!

1659
01:33:17,000 --> 01:33:20,000
<i>They</i> did it! They spit
in the eye of the Almighty!

1660
01:33:20,100 --> 01:33:21,100
No!

1661
01:33:21,200 --> 01:33:23,300
- ( angry shouting )
- MACKEY: Get over there!

1662
01:33:23,900 --> 01:33:25,000
DAVID: No!

1663
01:33:25,100 --> 01:33:26,700
MACKEY: Judas!

1664
01:33:28,000 --> 01:33:29,000
OLLIE: Jim!

1665
01:33:29,100 --> 01:33:31,500
Kill him! String him up!

1666
01:33:34,600 --> 01:33:36,300
Stand up, you coward!

1667
01:33:36,400 --> 01:33:37,300
Unkh!

1668
01:33:37,400 --> 01:33:40,800
( scattered applause )

1669
01:33:40,900 --> 01:33:42,000
Jesus!

1670
01:33:45,000 --> 01:33:46,200
DAVID: No!

1671
01:33:46,300 --> 01:33:47,700
Aaaahhhh!

1672
01:33:47,800 --> 01:33:49,900
MACKEY: Expiation!

1673
01:33:50,000 --> 01:33:51,600
- No!
- MAN: Stab him!

1674
01:33:53,200 --> 01:33:55,100
- Aaahhhh!
- Expiation!

1675
01:33:55,200 --> 01:33:57,900
Feed him to the beast!

1676
01:33:57,900 --> 01:33:59,900
Expiation!

1677
01:34:00,000 --> 01:34:04,000
Let the abominations
smell his blood!

1678
01:34:05,500 --> 01:34:07,100
No, no! No!

1679
01:34:07,200 --> 01:34:09,800
Aaaaahhhhh!

1680
01:34:09,900 --> 01:34:13,100
- Jesus! Wait!
- No, David!

1681
01:34:17,800 --> 01:34:20,300
Aaahhhh!

1682
01:34:20,400 --> 01:34:22,900
( crowd screaming and shouting )

1683
01:34:27,600 --> 01:34:30,100
( groans )

1684
01:34:31,200 --> 01:34:32,900
Aaahhhh!

1685
01:34:33,000 --> 01:34:36,400
( weeping )

1686
01:34:37,500 --> 01:34:39,000
( groaning and gasping )

1687
01:34:40,900 --> 01:34:42,400
( door locks )

1688
01:34:42,500 --> 01:34:44,500
Aah! Aaahhh!

1689
01:34:44,600 --> 01:34:47,600
Aaahhhh!

1690
01:34:48,700 --> 01:34:50,700
Aaahhh! Aah!

1691
01:34:50,800 --> 01:34:53,100
( monster roars )

1692
01:35:09,800 --> 01:35:11,200
Please.

1693
01:35:12,300 --> 01:35:14,200
( onlookers scream )

1694
01:35:15,500 --> 01:35:17,300
( distant monster roars )

1695
01:35:21,900 --> 01:35:24,500
MRS. CARMODY:
The beast will leave us alone tonight.

1696
01:35:26,000 --> 01:35:27,200
Tomorrow...

1697
01:35:28,400 --> 01:35:30,900
tomorrow, we'll just
have to wait and see.

1698
01:35:40,200 --> 01:35:41,400
BILLY: ( softly ) Daddy.

1699
01:35:43,100 --> 01:35:44,200
Daddy.

1700
01:35:56,100 --> 01:35:57,900
( softly ) Sorry I left you, pal.

1701
01:36:00,200 --> 01:36:01,900
I'll never leave you again.

1702
01:36:03,200 --> 01:36:04,400
Promise?

1703
01:36:05,800 --> 01:36:09,500
But you have to give me
your best promise, okay?

1704
01:36:09,600 --> 01:36:13,000
Your very best promise,
and can never break it.

1705
01:36:13,100 --> 01:36:14,800
Tell me.

1706
01:36:16,500 --> 01:36:18,900
Promise you won't let
the monsters get me.

1707
01:36:22,600 --> 01:36:24,700
Ever. No matter what.

1708
01:36:26,400 --> 01:36:27,900
I promise.

1709
01:36:31,100 --> 01:36:32,900
I love you, Daddy.

1710
01:36:33,000 --> 01:36:34,900
I love you, Billy.

1711
01:36:35,900 --> 01:36:37,200
More than anything.

1712
01:37:06,900 --> 01:37:08,100
( softly ) It's dawn.

1713
01:37:13,500 --> 01:37:16,400
Hey, pal, you ready to go home?

1714
01:37:16,400 --> 01:37:17,800
Come on.

1715
01:37:20,200 --> 01:37:23,200
Okay, I got the groceries
hidden at check stand number two.

1716
01:37:23,300 --> 01:37:25,800
Five bags. We can grab 'em
and get out the door.

1717
01:37:25,900 --> 01:37:27,200
Okay.

1718
01:37:27,200 --> 01:37:31,000
My car's parked in the center lane
of the parking lot, far end.

1719
01:37:31,000 --> 01:37:33,200
Whoever gets there first,
open up both doors,

1720
01:37:33,300 --> 01:37:36,000
and we'll all pile in
as fast as we can, okay?

1721
01:37:36,000 --> 01:37:37,200
Let's go.

1722
01:38:00,600 --> 01:38:02,800
Stealing food now?

1723
01:38:07,000 --> 01:38:09,000
Going out now, Mrs. Carmody.

1724
01:38:10,400 --> 01:38:12,000
Please stand aside.

1725
01:38:13,400 --> 01:38:16,000
You can't go out.
I won't allow it.

1726
01:38:16,100 --> 01:38:17,400
Won't allow it?

1727
01:38:17,500 --> 01:38:20,100
It's against God's will.

1728
01:38:20,200 --> 01:38:22,300
Don't you know that by now?

1729
01:38:22,400 --> 01:38:26,900
Haven't I proven myself
again and again and again?

1730
01:38:27,000 --> 01:38:31,500
Haven't I shown that I am His vessel?

1731
01:38:36,400 --> 01:38:37,900
What's the matter with you?

1732
01:38:41,200 --> 01:38:42,600
Don't you believe in God?

1733
01:38:43,600 --> 01:38:45,200
No one's interfered with you.

1734
01:38:45,300 --> 01:38:47,900
All we're asking for
is the same privilege.

1735
01:38:48,000 --> 01:38:49,300
You heard him.

1736
01:38:50,900 --> 01:38:54,900
It is these people
who brought this upon us.

1737
01:38:56,100 --> 01:39:01,100
They-- people who refused
to bend to the will of God,

1738
01:39:01,200 --> 01:39:03,800
and claim it privilege.

1739
01:39:03,900 --> 01:39:06,900
Sinners in pride.

1740
01:39:07,000 --> 01:39:09,000
Yes, haughty.

1741
01:39:09,100 --> 01:39:11,100
Privileged!

1742
01:39:11,200 --> 01:39:15,000
They mock us. They mock our--
our God, our faith,

1743
01:39:15,100 --> 01:39:18,500
our values, our very lifestyle.

1744
01:39:18,600 --> 01:39:20,800
They mock our humility

1745
01:39:20,900 --> 01:39:22,800
and our piousness.

1746
01:39:22,900 --> 01:39:25,900
They piss on us and laugh.

1747
01:39:29,200 --> 01:39:34,400
It's from them the blood
of human sacrifice must come.

1748
01:39:34,500 --> 01:39:36,500
From them...

1749
01:39:36,500 --> 01:39:39,100
- Come on.
- ...the blood of expiation.

1750
01:39:39,200 --> 01:39:40,200
JIM: Come on.

1751
01:39:40,300 --> 01:39:41,800
You try it.

